    "b-editor-scoping-note-37": {
      "id": "b-editor-scoping-note-37",
      "flavour": "implementation",
      "props": {
        "title": "Hotkey scoping: no-op while typing"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "All bindings in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "useCanvasHotkeys",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/editor/use-canvas-hotkeys.ts",
              "symbol": "useCanvasHotkeys"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " no-op when "
        },
        {
          "insert": "document.activeElement",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is an input, textarea, select, or contentEditable element ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "isEditableTarget",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), or when the caller's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "isTypingContextActive()",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " callback reports true — the editor wires this to whether the in-place text editor or connector-label editor currently has focus. Both checks exist because the inline editors own the keyboard while focused, but focus can lag a render, so the callback is a defensive second guard. Space is deliberately NOT bound in this hook at all — "
        },
        {
          "insert": "useCanvasViewport",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/editor/use-canvas-viewport.ts"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " owns space-drag panning separately, with its own space-held tracking. Anyone adding a new binding to "
        },
        {
          "insert": "TOOL_KEY_MAP",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " or the keydown handler gets this scoping for free by construction (the guard runs first, before any key is dispatched) — but a new hotkey that needs to fire even while typing (there currently are none) would need its own explicit carve-out, not a change to the shared guard."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
